; background-clip: initial;\">A group of six member delegates from Land Development Operation of Royal Project Foundation (RPF), Thailand visited the centre on 19<font face=\"Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.7em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial;\">th</span>&nbsp;of July, ’19. The team met with Program Director (PD) and the heads of different technical units. A short presentation was made by the PD highlighting on the vision, missions, and mandates of this centre along with some important deliberations on how this centre functions. The two parties had an opportunity to share different views on; staff capacity building, bio-technology enhancement, and some other important issues, to ensure further strengthening of ongoing collaborative activities.</font></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The team is here in Bhutan to continue collaborative activities and provide necessary technical support to Royal Projects as per the MoU signed between RPF, Thailand and the Ministry of Agriculture and Forests, Bhutan.</p>','2020-03-23',8,NULL,0),(15,'Visit of Land Development Department Delegation','Others','A Delegation of 7 members from the Land Development Department (LDD) of Thailand met with the Director, Department of Agriculture and they also visited NSSC.','<p>A Delegation of 7 members from the Land Development Department (LDD) of Thailand met with the Director, Department of Agriculture and they also visited NSSC. Under the Joint Agriculture Working Group MoU signed between the Ministry of Agriculture and Cooperatives, Thailand and MoAF, a project on soil mapping for Bhutan is being implemented jointly by NSSC and LDD. The two agencies continued to have a good working relation for almost 10 to 15 years. Discussion on possible areas of further collaboration included organic inputs and land development.<br></p>','2020-03-23',11,NULL,0),(16,'Fare-thee-well D.B Sir','Others','We tend to take everything and everyone for granted until such time when we either have to give up or part from each other, and only then we realize the value but by then it is too late for anything, really!','<p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">We tend to take everything and everyone for granted until such time when we either have to give up or part from each other, and only then we realize the value but by then it is too late for anything, really!</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">It is with a very heavy heart that the National Soil Services Centre bid farewell to Mr. D.B. Tamang who superannuated at the end of June 2019 after 36 years of his dedicated service to Tsa-Wa-Sum. He has been a huge strength of the Centre with his support especially towards the administrative work. By profession, he was Principal Research Officer, but he has been functioning as the IT personnel, Procurement Officer, MTO, Data Manger, Office Secretary, Officiating PD, etc. all wrapped in one. How an organization functions depend a lot on the cooperation of its staff and the strength of its Administration and Finance division. Mr. D.B. Tamangs contribution to the administration part has been immeasurable. With his exit from the NSSC, a vacuum has been created in the centre, but hopeful that our new Administrative Assistant will pick up the thread and fill up the vacuum. A refined gentleman, who was always in the office before anyone else in the morning to start off his day quietly, will be greatly missed.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">On behalf of the Department and the Ministry, the NSSC sincerely acknowledges his contributions and wishes him and his family a very happy, peaceful and content retired life ahead.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Tashi Delek!</p>','2020-03-23',8,NULL,0),(17,'ADIEU NSSC!!!  ','Others',' Having spent two thirds of my active service life totaling 36 years serving the nation with my best possible capabilities at the National Soil Services Center at Simtokha....\n                ','                                        <p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Having spent two thirds of my active service life totaling 36 years serving the nation with my best possible capabilities at the National Soil Services Center at Simtokha, the time to bid farewell to the NSSC Family came without realizing and quite fast, because of which, I have to exit from the civil service from 1<font face=\"Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.7em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial;\">st</span> July19.</font></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">My career in the civil service began in June 1983 with the appointment (on a temporary basis) at the erstwhile Royal Veterinary Diagnostic Laboratory under Department of Animal Husbandry at Serbithang. In January 1984, the appointment was regularized confirming my position as a Trainee Officer in Grade 12 until the end of the year after which I was upgraded to Grade 9 as Assistant Research Officer from 1<span style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial; font-size: 0.7em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">st</span> January 1985 attached to Feed Analysis Laboratory. Ten years later, the switch in working place occurred.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Owing to policy changes and resultant reshuffling exercise within the Ministry, the feed analysis laboratory was merged with Soil & Plant Analytical Laboratory at Simtokha in November 1993.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">During the 8<span style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial; font-size: 0.7em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">th</span> Plan, the inception of donor funded projects at Simtokha resulted in the growth of staff as well as the expansion of soil activities besides the analytical work on soil, plant, water and animal feeds – the growth leading to the up-gradation of the laboratory to the existing Center with its own administration and accounts. Due to human resource constraints, I had to shoulder the responsibilities of an administrative officer in addition to my own technical responsibilities of a feed analyst which continued until 2008 when the feed analysis facility was transferred to National Feed & Fodder Development Center in Bumthang. Since then, I was fully engaged in the administration services of the Center assisting in the smooth implementation of donor funded projects like SLMP funded by GEF/UNDP and a 6-year SLM Project funded by GEF/World Bank.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">During my very enjoyable tenure here, I have had the opportunity to work with excellent supervision and cooperation from all members of the “NSSC Family” including expatriates hired for the projects over the years. Thank you for the support, guidance and encouragement you all have provided me during my time at NSSC. Even though I will miss everyone at NSSC, I am looking forward to the new challenge of the new phase of my life as a retiree.</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Thank you again for a terrific time spanning 25<font face=\"Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 0.7em; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial;\">+</span> </font>years at NSSC!!! I wish every one of you all the best and hope to stay in touch.</p>                                    ','2020-03-23',6,NULL,1);

