kground-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 1.2em; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal;\">Services Provided:</h3><p style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px 0px 0px 25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline;\">- Assist clients in soil fertility management using information collected</p>  \n                  ',NULL,'2020-03-18',NULL),(19,'Land Management Unit ',NULL,5,'<p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial;\">Land Management Unit</span>&nbsp;(<font face=\"Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.3px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial;\">LMU</span>)</font></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">The Land Management Unit has been established from July 2013 after the termination of Sustainable Land Management Unit (2006-13) funded by GEF/World Bank that focused on three pilot Dzongkhags (Chukha, Trashigang &amp; Zhemgang). The Unit is mandated to provide technical backstopping to the activities initiated by the project and also assist in up-scaling them to other Dzongkhags.</p>  \n                  ',NULL,'2020-03-18',NULL),(20,'SLMP',NULL,6,'<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 1.2em; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 24px;\">Sustainable Land Management Project (SLMP)</span></h1><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><font face=\"Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.3px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial;\">Introduction</span></font><br><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial;\">The SLMP wasa six-year project (Februray 2006 to June 2012 – further extended to June 2013) funded by Global Environment Facility (GEF) through the World Bank with grant amount of USD 7.6m and parallel funding from DANIDA &amp; RGoB. The project, which was initiated as a response to the emerging land degradation problem in the country, washosted at the National Soil Services Centre (NSSC) under the Department of Agriculture, Ministry of Agriculture &amp; Forests (MoAF). The project details can be obtained from the Project Terminal Report available from the Center.</span></p>  \n                  ',NULL,NULL,9),(21,'MSP',NULL,6,'  \n                  <h1 style=\"margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0.1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; line-height: 1.2em; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">UNDP-GEF Medium Sized Project (MSP) on Sustainable Land Management (SLM)</span></h1><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">A UNDP-GEF project on “Capacity building and mainstreaming sustainable land management” wasa three year project (2007-2009) signed on 25th January 2007 and implementedby NSSC since the beginning from February 2007. The total budget of the project was USD 515,000 (USD 500,000 from GEF and USD 15, 000 from UNDP).</p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial; font-size: 14.3px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Project Objective</span><br><span style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">To build capacity in Sustainable Land Management (SLM) in appropriate government and civil society institutions and user groups and mainstream SLM into government planning and strategy development in Bhutan.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial; font-size: 14.3px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Project Outcome</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">- Completion of a National Action Program (NAP) on land degradation</p><p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">- Strengthening human resources and institutional capacities on SLM</p><p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">-Mainstreaming and harmonizing SLM into national policies, plans and economic development and environmental frameworks.</p><p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 1em; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><font face=\"Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 14.3px; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial;\"><i>Implementation responsibilities</i></span></font><br><span style=\"background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; border-style: initial; border-color: initial; border-image: initial; outline-color: initial; outline-style: initial;\">The Project wasexecuted by NSSC and complemented and shared lessons with the WB-GEF project on Sustainable Land Management (SLMP).</span></p>  \n                                    ',NULL,'2020-03-22',4);

